Options to connect to Databricks from AI code assist tools
Connect non‑Databricks clients to Databricks MCP servers:
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/databricks/generative-ai/mcp/connect-external-services

AI Dev Kit VS Code installation instructions
https://github.com/databricks-solutions/ai-dev-kit

Claude Desktop config file additions:


{
  "mcpServers": {
    "databricks": {
      "command": "uv",
      "args": [
        "run",
        "--directory",
        "C:\\Users\\YourAccountName\\.ai-dev-kit\\repo\\databricks-mcp-server",
        "python",
        "run_server.py"
      ],
      "env": {
        "DATABRICKS_HOST": "ENTER-DATABRICKS-WORKSPACE-URL-HERE",
        "DATABRICKS_TOKEN": "ENTER-DATABRICKS-PAT-TOKEN-HERE"
      }
    }
  },
  "preferences": {
    "coworkScheduledTasksEnabled": true,
    "ccdScheduledTasksEnabled": true,
    "sidebarMode": "chat",
    "coworkWebSearchEnabled": false
  }
}
pyproject.toml file edits (in the AI Dev Kit repo):

Edit the Python requirement:


requires-python = ">=3.10"
Add at the bottom:


[tool.uv.sources]
databricks-tools-core = { path = "../databricks-tools-core" }
